  "prompt": "Where can I get audiobooks for free in English?",
  "response": "There are several sites and platforms where you can find free audiobooks in English. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **LibriVox**: Offers thousands of public domain audiobooks read by volunteers. You can listen online or download.\n\n2. **Project Gutenberg**: Known primarily for its eBooks, Project Gutenberg also has a selection of audiobooks (both human-read and computer-generated) that are in the public domain.\n\n3. **Open Culture**: This site curates a list of free audiobooks (among other educational resources) available from various sources.\n\n4. **Audible Free Trials**: Audible often offers free trials that allow you to access audiobooks for free for a limited time. Just remember to cancel if you don't want to continue the subscription.\n\n5. **Spotify**: Some users upload audiobooks on Spotify, allowing you to listen for free (with ads) or with a premium subscription.\n\n6. **YouTube**: Many audiobooks can be found for free on YouTube. Just search for the title you're interested in.\n\n7. **Internet Archive**: This digital library offers a vast collection of audiobooks, including classic literature and newer titles.\n\n8. **Libby and OverDrive**: If you have a library card, you can borrow audiobooks for free through these apps, which connect to your local library's digital collection.\n\n9. **Scribl**: A platform that provides free audiobooks, often by emerging authors. You can find a selection of free works supported by a pay-what-you-want model for others.\n\nAlways make sure to check the copyright status and ensure that the audiobooks you're accessing are legally available for free.",
